	<Title>
		Blood pressure tip: Get off the couch
	</Title>
	<Body>
		&lt;p&gt;If you&apos;re concerned about high blood pressure, consider this: 30 to 60 minutes of physical activity most days of the week can lower your blood pressure by 4 to 9 millimeters of mercury (mm Hg). And it doesn&apos;t take long to see a difference. If you&apos;ve been sedentary, increasing your activity can lower your blood pressure within just a few weeks. So what are you waiting for? Talk to your doctor about starting an exercise program.&lt;/p&gt;
